            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Like many of Sid Meier's games, this one is also terribly bugged. You can't end the game with space travel - bug black screen. No matter the option you choose, you can't do some things in-game, the rules that you are capable of changing don't change in reality, just making them twistedly bugged, so the game becomes a minefield. Despite I like Sid Meier's games, all of them follow this pattern - bugs, bugs, bugs."
